    "naive": "Find all patients with cataracts.",
    "broad": "Find all patients diagnosed with any form of cataract \u2014 including the parent cataract concept, bilateral cataracts (both eyes affected), unilateral cataracts (one eye affected), and nuclear cataracts (the most common age-related morphology).",
    "expert": "I need to identify all cataract patients. Cataracts are documented under multiple SNOMED codes: Cataract (193570009) is the parent disorder, with laterality variants Bilateral cataracts (95722004) and Unilateral cataract (95721006), plus morphology-specific Nuclear cataract (53889007). Search Condition resources for these codes."
